Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the logical complexity of planar graphs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the computability of a canonic form of planar graphs. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper mentions the complexity class $AC^1$ in relation to the planar graph isomorphism problem. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper deals with planar graphs, which are a subset of computational geometry. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also possible as the paper deals with graph theory and the definability of planar graphs.
